{
  "text": "Moreover, the VDR gene promoter was characterized and found to include potential binding sites for specific transcriptional regu-lators such as AP-1 and NFkB, which could mediate phorbol ester inducibility [CITATION_1] . Phorbol esters are a group of compounds whose actions are mediated in part by PKC. At present, 11 isotypes of PKC are known to feature different cell type pattern of expression, suggesting characteristic functions for each PKC isoform [CITATION_2] . We have found that PKCg isoform mRNA is only expressed by K562 cells and is absent in the other two cell lines (data not shown). This variability could also account for the different responses of VDR expression elicited by PMA in these leukemic cell lines.",
  "correct_citation": {
